    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is an exceptional 2003 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, finished in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been meticulously serviced. Power is delivered via a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M Differential Lock. Crucially, the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced with structural plates, and the rod bearings have been replaced to ensure mechanical longevity. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, utilizing fresh OEM dampers and bushings to preserve the legendary handling balance. The exterior maintains its original luster with no signs of clear coat failure or oxidation, while the interior features pristine Nappa leather with zero bolster wear. This is a concours-level example for the discerning driver who values mechanical transparency and chassis integrity.",
